    <note type="biography">
        <p>Naval officer. Entered the merchant navy in 1840. Entered service with the Cunard line in 1851. Commanded the steamer <hi rend="italic">Great Eastern</hi> during the laying of the Atlantic telegraph, 1865–6. Managing director, Eastern Telegraph Company, 1866–93. Fellow of the Royal Geographical Society, 1870. Knighted, 1866.</p></note>
